Jharkhand: Man commits suicide as wedding gets postponed due to lockdown

Crime
Mirror Now Digital
Updated May 27, 2020 | 06:13 IST

A 30-year-old man allegedly ended his life as his wedding date got postponed due to the ongoing lockdown.

Man ended life as his wedding got postponed due to lockdown  |  Photo Credit: ANI

Key Highlights

  • After the postponement of the wedding day, the now-deceased man stopped talking to his family and friends
  • At around 4 am on Sunday, the now-deceased man's father found him hanging with a ceiling fan in the living room of their house
  • Before the man's death, his father had lost two other sons

Jamshedpur: In a shocking case, a 30-year-old man allegedly committed suicide by hanging himself from a ceiling fan at his house at Vishwakarma Nagar in Jamshedpurs Mango suburb on Sunday. Reportedly, the man was deeply stressed as his wedding was indefinitely postponed, according to the police.

The incident took place within the territorial jurisdiction of the Olidih Police Station. The deceased man was identified as Sanjit Gupta. The police have registered a case of suicide and are investigating the matter. The body of the deceased man was sent to MGM for conducting postmortem examination, a source said.

According to a report by The Times of India, the deceased man went to his room after having dinner on Saturday night. At around 4 am when his father Rajendra Prasad Gupta woke up to use the washroom, he found Sanjit hanging from the ceiling fan in the living room of their house.

Inconsolable father waits outside postmortem room

The deceased mans father waited outside the post mortem room of the hospital to collect his sons body. He broke down inconsolably. He said that his sons marriage was fixed with a girl from Bihars Aurangabad and the couple scheduled to tie the knot on April 25. However, the wedding date was postponed due to the imposition of the nationwide lockdown in the wake of rising COVID-19 cases. The wedding date postponement affected Sanjit in an adverse manner, Rajendra added.

Ahmedabad: Man attempts suicide after disagreement with wife over lunch menu-WATCH

Man loses third son

After the postponement of marriage date, Sanjit, who ran a grocery store, got depressed and stopped speaking with his family and friends. His father told TOI that Sanjit blamed the lockdown for spoiling the plans of his marriage and developed suicidal tendencies. He made several attempts to pacify him but he refused to listen to him. Rajendra had lost two other sons before Sanjits death. One of his sons had drowned in the year 2000 and another had gone missing in 2012.
